doc_summary_long: Venezuela's supreme court has reversed the decision to strip congress of its legislative powers that sparked protests in the country and widespread international condemnation. The move had drawn criticism at home and abroad that the South American country was no longer a democracy, prompting calls from the UN and elsewhere for it to be reconsidered. Venezuela's top prosecutor condemns court move to strip congress of power.
doc_summary_short: Venezuela's supreme court has reversed the decision to strip congress of its legislative powers that sparked protests in the country and widespread international condemnation.
doc_title: Venezuela reverses ruling to strip congress of legislative powers
